# üî∑ PART 3 ‚Äî The 45-Minute Interview Framework

Use this structure every time.

---

## Step 1 ‚Äî Requirements (5‚Äì10 mins)

### Functional

What must the system do?

### Non-functional

* Latency (e.g., <500ms)
* Availability (99.99%?)
* Consistency (Strong vs Eventual)
* Throughput (QPS)
* Durability

---

## Step 2 ‚Äî Back-of-the-envelope Estimation (5 mins)

Estimate:

* DAU
* Read/write ratio
* QPS
* Storage/year
* Bandwidth

---

## Step 3 ‚Äî API Design (5 mins)

Example:

```
POST /tweet
GET /feed
POST /payment
```

---

## Step 4 ‚Äî High-Level Architecture (10 mins)

Client ‚Üí DNS ‚Üí Load Balancer ‚Üí App Servers ‚Üí DB / Cache / MQ

---

## Step 5 ‚Äî Deep Dive (15 mins)

* Sharding strategy
* Caching strategy
* Data model
* Queue usage
* Failure handling

---

## Step 6 ‚Äî Bottlenecks & Trade-offs (5 mins)

* Hot keys?
* 10x traffic?
* Regional failure?
* DB crash?
* Consistency compromise?

---

